  <section id="meta-tags">
    <h2>3. Meta Tags Tasks</h2>

    <h3>3.1 â€” Example page already contains 5 meta tags</h3>
    <p>(charset, viewport, description, keywords, author are included in the &lt;head&gt; of this page.)</p>

    <h3>3.2 â€” Add a favicon to a page</h3>
    <p>See the &lt;link rel="icon"&gt; in the &lt;head&gt; â€” replace href with your favicon URL or file path:</p>
    <pre>&lt;link rel="icon" href="path/to/favicon.png" type="image/png"&gt;</pre>

    <h3>3.3 â€” Meta tags for a portfolio website (example)</h3>
    <pre>
&lt;meta name="description" content="Portfolio of John Doe - Web Developer, UI/UX Designer"&gt;
&lt;meta name="keywords" content="portfolio, web developer, front-end, react, javascript"&gt;
&lt;meta name="author" content="John Doe"&gt;
&lt;meta name="robots" content="index,follow"&gt;
&lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"&gt;
    </pre>

    <h3>3.4 â€” Meta tags for a shopping website (example)</h3>
    <pre>
&lt;meta name="description" content="ShopZone - Best deals on electronics, fashion and home appliances"&gt;
&lt;meta name="keywords" content="shop, ecommerce, deals, electronics, fashion"&gt;
&lt;meta name="author" content="ShopZone Team"&gt;
&lt;meta name="robots" content="index,follow"&gt;
&lt;meta property="og:title" content="ShopZone - Great Deals Today"&gt;
&lt;meta property="og:description" content="Buy top brands at best prices. Free shipping on orders over $50."&gt;
    </pre>

    <h3>Notes</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Open Graph (og:) meta tags help link previews on social platforms.</li>
      <li>Use a real favicon file path for correct display in browsers.</li>
      <li>Replace example meta content with your actual project data for SEO.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

